In this press briefing, President Trump discusses various topics including the situation in Puerto Rico, the criticism of officials in Puerto Rico, the response to Hurricane Maria, the investigation into Secretary Tom Price's use of private planes, the search for a new Homeland Security Secretary, and the controversy surrounding NFL players kneeling during the national anthem. The President expresses his disappointment with Secretary Price's use of private planes and indicates that a decision will be made about his future in the Cabinet. He also mentions the ongoing efforts to rebuild Puerto Rico and the need for a long-term plan. The President confirms that he has spoken to NFL team owners about the national anthem controversy and expresses his satisfaction with reports that all players stood for the anthem at a recent game.